# 📖 Data Dictionary - Aviation Analytics

This dictionary explains the variables used to analyze international flight patterns and passenger volumes.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Operating_Airline** | String | The airline actually flying the aircraft (e.g., Delta, Emirates). |
| **GEO_Region** | String | Global geographic area (e.g., Middle East, Europe, Central America). |
| **Activity_Period** | Date/YYYYMM | The month and year the data was recorded. |
| **Passenger_Count** | Integer | Total number of passengers on that specific route/period. |
| **Price_Category** | String | Classification of the airline (Low-Fare vs. Other). |
| **Terminal / Boarding_Area** | String | Specific airport location where the activity occurred. |

*Note: All passenger counts were aggregated to the monthly level to identify seasonal trends.*
